TITLE: Connecting to Browserbase with Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to connect to Browserbase using Puppeteer. It establishes a connection using the Browserbase API key, creates a new page, navigates to the Browserbase website, and then properly closes both the page and browser.
SOURCE: https://github.com/browserbase/docs/blob/main/quickstart/puppeteer.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import puppeteer from "puppeteer-core";

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.connect({
    browserWSEndpoint:
    `wss://connect.browserbase.com?apiKey=${process.env.BROWSERBASE_API_KEY}`
  });

  const page = await browser.newPage();

  await page.goto("https://www.browserbase.com");
  await page.close();
  await browser.close();
})().catch((error) => console.error(error.message));
```

