TITLE: Session Lifecycle State Diagram in Mermaid
DESCRIPTION: A Mermaid diagram that illustrates the state transitions of a Browserbase Session throughout its lifecycle, from creation to completion, including error handling and billing points.
SOURCE: https://github.com/browserbase/docs/blob/main/features/sessions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: mermaid
CODE:
```
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NEW
    ERROR --> [*]

    note left of ERROR
      Any error during the process moves the Session in ERROR state.

      (Billing ends here)
    end note

    note left of NEW
      Session created via the API
      or a Driver (connectOverCDP())
    end note

    NEW --> PENDING

    note right of PENDING
      The Session is waiting for a Browser instance.
    end note

    PENDING --> RUNNING

    note left of RUNNING
      The Session is ready to accept actions.
      (Billing begins here)
    end note

    RUNNING --> REQUEST_RELEASE: Note that a Session is released without connection under 15min
    REQUEST_RELEASE --> RELEASING

    note left of REQUEST_RELEASE
      The Session has been requested to stop.

      (Billing stops at this state completion)
    end note

    RELEASING --> COMPLETED
    COMPLETED --> [*]
```

